==English==

===Noun phrase===
'''gaseous phase'''
#{{physics}} One of the three fundamental [[structural]] [[phases]] of matter in which the thermal mobility of molecules or atoms is strong enough to permit their free motion, significantly exceeding the cohesive force.

====Usage notes====
*The word ''gaseous phase'' tends to be used when the [[statistical mechanical]] or [[thermodynamic]] nature of matter is focused on rather than the matter itself.

====Synonyms====
*[[gas]]

